10:54 <Enygma`> vmassol: I don`t remember now, but looking at http://platform.xwiki.org/xwiki/bin/view/DevGuide/Standard+URL+Format#HAction:view I see we`re missing some documentation

11:26 <Enygma`> vmassol: http://platform.xwiki.org/xwiki/bin/view/DevGuide/Standard+URL+Format?viewer=changes&rev1=85.2&rev2=86.2 please add anything missing  
11:26 <vmassol> checking thxs  
11:29 <vmassol> seems good Enygma  
11:29 <vmassol> maybe a small improvement would be to use somthing else than Space1 and Space2  
11:30 <vmassol> like Item1 and Item2 or Name1 and Name2  
11:30 <Enygma`> or Page1.Page2  
11:30 <vmassol> since they can either represent pages or spaces dpeending on the context  
11:30 <vmassol> yes or Page1 and Page2  
11:30 <vmassol> if we want to not show the concept of spaces  
11:30 <Enygma`> if talking about NP  
11:30 <vmassol> the rest of the doc talks about spaces though  
11:31 <Enygma`> hinting to the view action in http://www.xwiki.org/xwiki/bin/view/FAQ/How+can+I+get+the+reference+of+a+page?viewer=changes&rev1=3.2&rev2=3.6  
11:31 <vmassol> but I'm fine with any name  
11:31 <vmassol> just that space1 space2 don't seem the best choice (I know it was me who put it probably ;))  
11:31 <Enygma`> yeah, would be a bit too much of a change to do for the entire doc maybe  
11:31 <vmassol> thanks for the hint  
11:32 <Enygma`> for the FAQ entry, I feel that pointing to the URL format might be a bit too abstract/technical  
11:33 <vmassol> probably, OTOH it gives the full answer  
11:34 <vmassol> I don't fully visualize how hard it is to understand it for a newvie  
11:34 <Enygma`> :) that`s probably the problem I fear :)  
11:34 <Enygma`> but I would also not want to duplicate things  
11:34 <vmassol> \*newbie

11:34 <vmassol> well the right solution is what is mentioned in the FAQ  
11:35 <vmassol> ie what Ance was working on  
11:35 <vmassol> ie http://jira.xwiki.org/browse/XWIKI-13362  
11:35 <Enygma`> maybe we should have this general practice mentioned and then say, for the full details and edge cases, see the URL format specification  
11:35 <vmassol> lucaa: any idea if you'll be to finish this ? :)  
11:35 <Enygma`> since some might want to avoid that technical doc

11:48 <vmassol> ok  
11:49 <vmassol> we hid the tour and I think we should hide those as well. In general we should hide the apps we provide and leave it empty for users to have their own apps in there and not touch the default apps  
11:49 <evalica> vmassol: the apps are from Demo Content - the idea was to be visible since they are not technical, but the user should see/use them

11:50 <vmassol> A user may not go throught he help cetner  
11:50 <vmassol> and may go to AWM

11:51 <vmassol> (as a user-  
11:51 <vmassol> )  
11:52 <vmassol> I certanly don't want to see those apps  
11:52 <vmassol> they're only interesting for the evaluator persona  
11:52 <evalica> I'll talk with mflorea and see what we can do

11:52 <vmassol> ok thx  
11:52 <evalica> thx  
11:53 <vmassol> (ie have permissions to delete them)  
11:53 <vmassol> the last author should also be modified BTW  
11:53 <vmassol> normally all apps that we bundle have the Admin user

11:54 <vmassol> (this is even chcked by the build )  
11:54 <vmassol> ah yes  
11:54 <vmassol> makes sense then  
12:01 <mflorea> vmassol: those apps are hidden by default, see https://github.com/xwiki-contrib/application-help-center/blob/master/src/main/resources/Help/Applications/Contributors/WebHome.xml but they become visible when they are edited. It just means that someone edited the apps on playground.  
12:01 <mflorea> (there's no UIExtension object on the app home page to put the icon on the app bar)  
12:01 <mflorea> I removed the UIX object explicitly for this  
12:02 <vmassol> Caty has imported them as XAR  
12:02 <mflorea> but the object is added back when you edit the app  
12:02 <vmassol> is thay why they're visible in the AWM LT?  
12:02 <vmassol> I don't see anyone else who has edited them  
12:03 <mflorea> they are AWM apps so yes, they are visible on the AWM LT. I was referring to the app bar, not to he livetable  
12:03 <vmassol> http://playground.xwiki.org/xwiki/bin/view/Main/AllDocs#|t=alldocs&p=1&l=15&s=doc.date&d=asc&doc.location=Help  
12:03 <vmassol> ok I was only talking about AWM LT  
12:03 <mflorea> then I don't agree with you  
12:03 <vmassol> they're only for the evaluator person  
12:03 <vmassol> Persona  
12:03 <vmassol> and they should not leak to the other persona  
12:03 <mflorea> they should be visible on the AWM live table because they are demo content  
12:03 <vmassol> no  
12:03 <vmassol> only for the eval persona  
12:04 <mflorea> same as the BlogIntroduction is visible on the blog  
12:04 <vmassol> yes that too  
12:04 <vmassol> but  
12:04 <vmassol> for the blog post it's easy to delete it  
12:04 <vmassol> is it the same for those apps? who can delete them?  
12:04 <vmassol> (that was the question I asked above)  
12:05 <vmassol> basically we need to make it clear to users  
12:05 <vmassol> - when content is demo content  
12:05 <mflorea> any admin can delete them, there are no special right set on them  
12:05 <vmassol> - with instructions on how to remove them easily  
12:05 <mflorea> but they are part of the help center app  
12:05 <vmassol> the home page can also be considered demo content btw  
12:06 <mflorea> and the idea is that you remove the demo content app, not delete just some of its pages  
12:06 <vmassol> I don't fully agree with this  
12:06 <vmassol> if I'm an admin  
12:06 <vmassol> I'd like to keep the help center for my users  
12:06 <vmassol> but I don't want demo content to leak into the wiki  
12:06 <mflorea> those app are part of the help center  
12:07 <vmassol> yes that's why theys hould be contained th'ere  
12:07 <vmassol> and not leak  
12:07 <vmassol> the help center is useful  
12:07 <vmassol> and in most cases I'll expect admins to keep it  
12:07 <vmassol> since that's documentation  
12:07 <vmassol> however when you start using your wiki for real  
12:08 <vmassol> you don't want to see demo content in standard places  
12:08 <mflorea> again, those apps are part of the help center, if the help center is useful then those apps are useful too  
12:08 <mflorea> otherwise we wouldn't include them in the help center  
12:08 <vmassol> grr  
12:08 <vmassol> you don't want to understand so I'm repeart it once more  
12:09 <vmassol> the help center is usefu for users who want to go there and learn about it  
12:09 <vmassol> those apps showing up in the AWM LT when you use your wiki for real is bad  
12:09 <mflorea> I understand what you're saying, I just don't agree  
12:10 <vmassol> ok then we'll need other opinion since I don't see how someone cannot agree with what I said :)  
12:10 <mflorea> for me it's confusing to see the app in the help center and not in the AWM live table  
12:10 <vmassol> it seems so obvioius to me  
12:10 <vmassol> I'm not saying thaty  
12:10 <vmassol> I'm saying that it's ok for the eval persona but not after, when you start using your wiki for real  
12:11 <vmassol> and when you do so you don't want tor emove the help enter  
12:11 <vmassol> \*center  
12:11 <vmassol> but you do want to remove the demo content that is in standard places  
12:11 <vmassol> the demo content that is located in the Help space is ok tough  
12:11 <vmassol> since it's contained and not showing up in standard places  
12:11 <mflorea> when you're using the wiki for real you still go to the help center and you still see those apps there and so you still wonder why aren't those apps listed in the AWM live table is they are AWM apps  
12:12 <vmassol> I'm not giving your the answer marius  
12:13 <vmassol> :)  
12:13 <vmassol> I'm telling you the problem  
12:13 <mflorea> and I don't agree it's a problem  
12:13 <vmassol> what is not a problem? showing those apps even when you start using your wiki for real?  
12:14 <mflorea> those apps are located in the help center space, but the AWM live table looks everywhere. I can of course hide the home page of these apps to hide them from the AWM live table but I don't agree with this  
12:14 <vmassol> again this would be one solution and I didn't even menton it  
12:14 <vmassol> you did it  
12:14 <vmassol> I've not provided an answer!  
12:15 <vmassol> first I want to raise the problem and that we agree there's something to improve  
12:15 <vmassol> so "showing those apps even when you start using your wiki for real is ok for you?"?  
12:16 <mflorea> I mentioned it just to show you that I understand what you say but again I don't agree with you. To be clear: I don't think it's a problem that these apps appear in the AWM LT when you start using your wiki for real  
12:16 <vmassol> becauze if the answer is that admins should remove the help center to have those apps diappear then it's not a good solutoin  
12:16 <mflorea> I don't think admins have to remove these apps, because I don't think listing the apps in the AWM live table is a problem  
12:17 <vmassol> ok so you agree that our answer is that the admin is expected to remove those apps one by one if he doesn't want to see them but still keep the Help center?  
12:17 <vmassol> wow  
12:17 <vmassol> I don't believe you  
12:17 <vmassol> :)  
12:17 <vmassol> I'd like to see your own wioki  
12:17 <vmassol> wiki  
12:17 <vmassol> that contains demo content mixed with real content  
12:18 <vmassol> I can bet you'll have removed the demo content  
12:18 <vmassol> (knowing you)  
12:18 <mflorea> I need to go to lunch.  
12:18 <vmassol> I can bet you'll have changed the home page and that you'll have remove the first blog post too  
12:19 <vmassol> ok good lunch!  
12:19 <vmassol> let's see what others tihink too, that helps
